reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small and strong
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for what I needed in my hair salon…small, adjustable settings, quiet…perfect and blended right in to our decor

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and soothing
reviews.reviewText: It does a great job sitting on my desk and keeping me cool throughout the day. It's a little bit noisy, but it's a fan so of course it makes noise. I love the three levels, the light, and that fact that it doesn't have blades (the blades broke on my last desk fan and I was very sad when that happened). It will even blow cool air all the way across a small room on the highest setting, which I did not expect. I would definitely buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute and puts out more air than you know
reviews.reviewText: First let me say, that this is beyond cute. It has a light that you can tap on and change colors. There is minimal noise and resembles a Dyson, but much more affordable. It helps to circulate the air and puts out a gentle breeze. Great for small spaces. I use mine at work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought two of these fans. One for my mom and one for my 12yr son. My mom loves the speed selection and that it has no blades, is safe and quiet. My son likes the high speed as he says it gets him cold. He also enjoys the light colors. I needed something quiet and portable. They are great size and good price. Very durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cute but loud
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately I’m returning it because it’s loud and it didn’t allow me to sleep. ( light sleeper) The air is minimum, you can barely feel it. Even worst the light of the fan stays on. No, I’m not talking about the different color light you turn on. Its the official light when you turn the fan on. It’s cute and light weight but it didn’t wow me. :(

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not very strong
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this fan to replace an older fan I use in the bathroom. This fan looked like it produced good airflow on the videos so I figured I would try it. It was so disappointing. There is a little tiny fan in the base that pulls the air in and then that air blows out of the tube holes up top to produce the “bladeless airflow”. Even on the highest setting it blows very little. I would compare it to the low setting on a hairdryer and that’s being generous. I guess I just expected more from the videos that were advertised for it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewText: prefect for desk of night stand ,works wonders, im getting the bigger one soon

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I work from home most days and it has been really hot lately! My small apartment does not have AC sadly, and due to space as well as being on the phone throughout the day, my tower fan is too loud and bulky! I bought this little fan to sit it on my desk and to be quiet while I work. So far, it does what you’d expect! A light tap on the button turns it on, it has 3 different can settings, and a few different but fun colored light options. I can’t complain with this purchase. If you are interested in trying one out for yourself, be aware that this fan is not silent though! It still has a light hum on the lowest setting. I think it’s actually fairly calming. But I called my sister on my work phone to test if she could hear it.. And though not intensely, she definitely could hear it as background noise!Additionally, this fan is not built to cool down an entire room. Sure, it may work for people in small rooms or who like to have a light fan on at bed.. But if this product wasn’t on my desk where I am, I probably wouldn’t feel it too much. Still though! It’s a good little fan, and will get the job I need done. :)

reviews.reviewTitle: 200% love this fan. 10 stars if I could!
reviews.reviewText: 200% love this fan. It's quiet and does the job. 1 at home on my desk and 2 at work for us girls. We all love it!

My Lady, in menopause, needed a fan by her work desk that was quiet because her job is on the phone all day. When her hot flashes hit the fan cools her down. She loves it. Personally, I put my hands in front of it and it doesn't feel strong, but she swears by it. Happy wife, happy life. Lol.

reviews.reviewTitle: Nice little fan - Quiet but not silent
reviews.reviewText: We have this fan by the bedside and it is quiet as compares to a bladed, oscillating fan, but don't expect it to be silent. Overall, we're happy with it for the price. It would be nice if the lights could be turned off - this is more annoying than the sound level.
Worked great for a while but just stopped working after a couple months.

Okay purchase, a bit expensive for the product, but it is what you see in the pictures. Lights are very nice! The fan is quite weak, I put it at the end of my bed but I can barely feel it, even if it's on at full speed. only when i put it on a table and put my face 1 foot away from it will it be enough.
